$:/tweaks/cth/Macro/find.title: $:/tweaks/cth/Macro/find
$:/tweaks/cth/Macro/find.creator: Mohammad
$:/tweaks/cth/Macro/find.text:
\define find(text, begin, end, output:"simple", mode:"all") <$vars fulltext=<<__text__>> start=<<__begin__>> stop=<<__end__>> output-macro=<<__output__>> > <$list variable="p1" filter="[splitbefore]"> <$list variable="p2" filter="[removeprefix]"> <$list variable="p3" filter="[splitbeforeremovesuffix]"> <$macrocall $name=<> p=<> /> <$reveal type="match" text="all" default=<<__mode__>> > <$macrocall $name="find" text={{{[removeprefixremoveprefix]}}} begin=<> end=<> output=<> /> \end \define simple(p) <$text text=<<__p__>> /> \end \define simple-list(p)
  • <$text text=<<__p__>>/>
    • \end !! Macro <<< <> <<< !! Summary * `find` is a macro to search for a text snippet and find all snippets delimited between values of `begin` and `end` delimiters * `simple` is a macro used by `find` to show the output in a simple format * `simple-list` is a macro used by `find` to show the output in a simple list format. The ordered and unordered list can be used if the call to `find` macro wrapped in a `div` with suitable type e.g `ol` or `ul`. !! Revision ; Rev 2.0 : Date: Mar 21, 2019 : A new `mode` parameter to allow finding all snippets or only the first snippet ;Rev 1.0 : Date: Dec 28, 2018 : First release
